\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7756011 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 
Would you say any of them was an important influence on you?
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid13638963 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7756011 Glen:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\insrsid4470500\charrsid7756011 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 I think my mother\rquote s side of the family was \'85
 We would always, in the summer time, go up to an island in the Thousand Islands, right off of New York State, and that would be our summer vacation, [Boscabel Island] was owned by my grandparents and that family, and so I would see them ev}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13638963\charrsid7756011 ery summer, for quite a while. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 
And I never really had that experience with my other grandfather and grandmother.  So I did not know them nearly as well, I [mainly] remember them from photographs.  When I was growing up, my father\rquote 
s parents had moved to Florida and had purchased an orange grove, and they were doing that at the time.  But that was the only time that I can remember g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13638963\charrsid7756011 
oing there and visiting them.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 But with my mother\rquote s side of the family, it\rquote s kind of a classic tie between mothers and their families, much closer and \'85
 and typically vacations organised around that family, rather than around the father\rquote s family.  My father came from a smaller family, he 
was the only child, and my mother came from a family with two sisters and a brother.  So all of those people played a significant role in my life.  They\rquote 
ve all lived into their nineties.  My mother lived to be almost 94, and my two aunts were 92/93, and my uncle is the y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13638963\charrsid7756011 oungest and he is 90.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 
He was a graduate of Harvard University, got his Ph.D. in Economics, and worked for the Office of Price Administration during the War, under Galbraith.  He had quite a career in government, and then became very much in
volved in the international film industry, and has been retired for some time now.  But we feel very close to them, and they actually visited us in March this year [when Karen was ill].
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid9184388 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9184388\charrsid7756011 
