ve always thought that human ag
ency was a premise of symbolic interaction.  It was an underlying concept of the organism there.  In fact, if you go back to the sixties, you have behaviourism, which is a good example of people as pawns being shaped by the environment, and my psychologic
al friends would say, \'93Sociologists, like you, you\rquote re all happy about this (LAUGHS), except that it doesn\rquote t square with reality!\'94
