f a person-centred approach, where we view people, according to profiles that make sense, and we can also utilise their voice, their description of themselves, so that we have types of people, and we can think about how types of people change over time.  
Person-centred approaches are so well suited to the use of qualitative information, and they help to [provide] a real understanding of what a profile means, and how people think when they have this profile.  Without it, we don\rquote 
t really fully understand that.  And so the two come together very nicely in that regard.  
